# Pages & Routing Rules (src/app/**)

## Directory conventions (match this repo)
For a resource `blog-posts` (resource name `blog_posts`), the route structure is:

```
src/app/blog-posts/
├── page.tsx           # List (useTable)
├── layout.tsx         # Optional resource layout wrapper
├── create/page.tsx    # Create (useForm)
├── edit/[id]/page.tsx # Edit (useForm — action inferred from route)
└── show/[id]/page.tsx # Show (useShow)
```

Use the same pattern for new resources under `src/app/<resource>/...`.

## Page patterns (preferred)
- **List pages**: `useTable` + Ant Design `<Table>` inside `<List>`.
- **Create/Edit pages**: `useForm` + Ant Design `<Form>` inside `<Create>`/`<Edit>`. For fields linked to another resource, use `useSelect` from `@refinedev/antd` to get the dropdown options.
- **Show pages**: `useShow` inside `<Show>`. In Refine v5 `useShow` returns `{ result, query }` — `result` is the record data, `query` holds `isLoading` / `isError` state.
- All pages must be `"use client"` components (the data provider is client-side only).

## Data fetching
- Avoid `useEffect` for CRUD data.
- Prefer Refine hooks (which use `dataProvider`).

## Related data — choose ONE strategy, do not mix

**Option A — Supabase join via `meta.select` (preferred for read-only display):**
```tsx
const { tableProps } = useTable({
  meta: { select: "*, categories(id,title)" },
});
// Access directly: record.categories.title — no extra hook needed
```

**Option B — `useMany` (use when you need the full resource record or cross-resource logic):**
```tsx
const { data: categories } = useMany({ resource: "categories", ids: [...] });
```

**Never use both for the same relation.** The existing `src/app/blog-posts/page.tsx` (list) and `src/app/blog-posts/show/[id]/page.tsx` (show) both use `meta.select` join alongside `useMany`/`useOne` for the same relation — this is a known redundancy in the legacy code, not a pattern to follow. When writing new pages, pick one strategy.

## Auth pages
- Auth routes live under `src/app/login`, `src/app/register`, `src/app/forgot-password`.
- Don’t reimplement auth checks in pages; use `authProvider` and Refine routing/guards.
